{"format": "tiptap/v1", "updatedAt": "2026-06-22T04:04:06.739Z", "doc": {"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Cross-Validation"}, {"type": "text", "text": " is a statistical resampling technique that evaluates model performance by training and testing the model on "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "different subsets of data multiple times"}, {"type": "text", "text": ", providing a more reliable estimate of how well the model generalizes to unseen data than a single train-test split."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "What It Is"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Cross-validation partitions data into complementary subsets to enable "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "repeated training and validation cycles"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Key principle"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- Split data into subsets (folds)\n- Train on some subsets, test on remaining subsets\n- Repeat multiple times with different combinations\n- Average performance across all iterations"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Why it's better than residuals"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- Residuals don't indicate performance on "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "new predictions"}, {"type": "text", "text": "\n- Cross-validation tests on data the model hasn't seen\n- Checks how well model "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "generalizes"}, {"type": "text", "text": " to new data"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Why It's Important"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Benefit"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Explanation"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Generalization assessment"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Evaluates performance on independent data, prevents overfitting/underfitting"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Model selection"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Compares different models/hyperparameter settings to find the best"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Bias-variance trade-off"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Provides insights into model complexity vs. performance"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "More reliable estimate"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Better performance estimation than single train-test split"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Reduced variance"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "More stable metrics across different data splits"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Better data utilization"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Maximizes use of limited training data"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Protection against bias"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Reduces sampling bias from single split"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "K-Fold Cross-Validation (Most Common)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "K-fold cross-validation"}, {"type": "text", "text": " is the most commonly used method."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 4}, "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "How It Works"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "yaml"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Dataset: [●●●●●●●●●●] (10 samples)\nK = 5 folds\n\nFold 1: Train on [2,3,4,5], Test on  [cs.cmu](https://www.cs.cmu.edu/~schneide/tut5/node42.html)\nFold 2: Train on [1,3,4,5], Test on  [medium](https://medium.com/@mdsatriaalamshah/model-evaluation-cross-validation-2aae7de6767d)\nFold 3: Train on [1,2,4,5], Test on  [medium](https://medium.com/@shagunmistry/how-to-use-cross-validation-for-model-evaluation-in-machine-learning-fc2c9ff007e8)\nFold 4: Train on [1,2,3,5], Test on  [docs.aws.amazon](https://docs.aws.amazon.com/machine-learning/latest/dg/cross-validation.html)\nFold 5: Train on [1,2,3,4], Test on  [scikit-learn](https://scikit-learn.org/stable/modules/cross_validation.html)\n\nFinal score = Average of all 5 test scores"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Process"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n1. Dataset divided into "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "K equal-sized folds"}, {"type": "text", "text": "\n2. Repeat "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "K times"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": - Use "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "K-1 folds"}, {"type": "text", "text": " for training - Use "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "1 fold"}, {"type": "text", "text": " for validation\n3. Compute "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "average error"}, {"type": "text", "text": " across all K trials\n4. Final performance = average of K validation scores"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "For dataset D with n samples and k folds"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- Each fold contains: ~n/k samples\n- Training set size: ((k-1)/k) × n samples\n- Validation set size: n/k samples\n- Total training iterations: k"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Advantages of K-Fold over Holdout"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Holdout method"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (simplest cross-validation): Split once into train/test"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "K-Fold Advantage"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Explanation"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Matters less how data divides"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Every data point in test set exactly once, training set k-1 times"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Reduced variance"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Variance decreases as k increases"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "More data utilization"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "All data used for both training and validation"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Disadvantage"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Training algorithm must be rerun k times, taking "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "k times more computation"}, {"type": "text", "text": "."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Common K Values"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "K Value"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Use Case"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Notes"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "K=5"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Standard choice"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Good balance of speed and accuracy"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "K=10"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Common default"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "More reliable, slightly slower"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "K=3"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Very large datasets"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Faster, less iterations"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "K=n"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Small datasets (LOOCV)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Leave-one-out, maximal data use"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Rule"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Use minimum 30 samples per fold for statistical validity."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Other Cross-Validation Methods"}]}, {"type": "image", "attrs": {"src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,", "alt": "Cross-Validation — concept overview"}}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "1. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Stratified K-Fold"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Purpose"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Maintain class distribution across folds for "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "imbalanced datasets"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "How it works"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- Similar to K-Fold\n- Ensures each fold is "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "representative of overall class distribution"}, {"type": "text", "text": "\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Especially useful for imbalanced classification"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# Python implementation\nfrom sklearn.model_selection import StratifiedKFold\nskf = StratifiedKFold(n_splits=5, shuffle=True, random_state=42)"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "2. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Leave-One-Out (LOOCV)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Extreme K-fold"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": K = N (number of data points)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "How it works"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "N iterations"}, {"type": "text", "text": ", each uses "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "1 point as validation"}, {"type": "text", "text": ", rest as training\n- Average error = evaluation metric\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Computationally expensive"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (trains N times)\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Maximizes data use"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (uses all but 1 point for training)\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Good evaluation"}, {"type": "text", "text": " but expensive"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Use case"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Very small datasets where you need maximum data utilization."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "3. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Time Series Split"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Purpose"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Handle "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "temporal data"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (time series)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "How it works"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- Training "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "always precedes testing"}, {"type": "text", "text": " chronologically\n- Reflects real-world scenario where you predict future from past\n- Prevents \"peeking into the future\""}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# Python implementation\nfrom sklearn.model_selection import TimeSeriesSplit\ntscv = TimeSeriesSplit(n_splits=5, gap=0)"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "4. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Shuffle Split (Repeated Random)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Variant"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Randomly divide into test/training k different times"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Advantage"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- Independently choose test set size\n- Choose number of trials to average over\n- Flexible flexibility"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "When to Use Cross-Validation vs. Train/Val/Test"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Scenario"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Use"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Small datasets"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "k-fold cross-validation"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Limited data"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Cross-validation for better performance estimate"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Imbalanced classification"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Stratified K-Fold"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Time series data"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Time Series Split"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Large datasets"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Simple train/val/test split"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Very huge datasets"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Single train/test split (e.g., ImageNet 95%+ train)"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Rule"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Cross-validation is more reliable but computationally expensive; use when data is limited."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Implementation Example (Python)"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "from sklearn.model_selection import KFold\nfrom sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestClassifier\nfrom sklearn.datasets import load_iris\nimport numpy as np\n\n# Load data\nX, y = load_iris(return_X_y=True)\n\n# K-Fold setup\nkf = KFold(n_splits=5, shuffle=True, random_state=42)\n\n# Cross-validation\nscores = []\nfor train_idx, val_idx in kf.split(X):\n    X_train, X_val = X[train_idx], X[val_idx]\n    y_train, y_val = y[train_idx], y[val_idx]\n    \n    model = RandomForestClassifier()\n    model.fit(X_train, y_train)\n    score = model.score(X_val, y_val)\n    scores.append(score)\n\n# Average score\nprint(f\"Average accuracy: {np.mean(scores):.3f}\")\nprint(f\"Std dev: {np.std(scores):.3f}\")"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key Takeaways"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Cross-validation"}, {"type": "text", "text": " = resampling technique that trains/tests on different subsets multiple times"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "K-Fold"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (most common): Split into K folds, train on K-1, test on 1, repeat K times, average"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Better than holdout"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Every point in test set once, training set k-1 times, reduced variance"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Stratified K-Fold"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Maintains class distribution for imbalanced datasets"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "LOOCV"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": K=N (leave-one-out), maximizes data use, computationally expensive [web=242]"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Time Series Split"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Training precedes testing chronologically for temporal data"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Use when"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Small datasets, limited data, need better performance estimate"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Don't use when"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Large datasets (use train/val/test split)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "K=5 or 10"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Standard choices for good balance"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Cost"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": k times more computation (train k times)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Cross-validation is the \"reliable performance estimator\" — by repeatedly training and testing on different data folds and averaging results, it provides a more stable and trustworthy estimate of model generalization than a single split, especially valuable when data is limited, though it requires k times more computation for k-fold."}]}]}}